<p>I have a <code>2D array</code> of varying <strong>size</strong>, where <code>height</code> can take on any value.</p>  <pre><code>int array[][] = new int[height][height] </code></pre>  <p>Let's say I have a <code>3 x 3 array</code> with the values of:</p>  <pre><code>7 8 9  6 5 4  1 2 3 </code></pre>  <p>Would it be possible to check to see if <strong>1 is adjacent to 2</strong>, <strong>2 adjacent to 3</strong>, <strong>3 adjacent to 4</strong>, <strong>4 adjacent to 5</strong> and <strong>so on</strong>? </p>  <p>Adjacent here being if they are next to each other <code>vertically</code>, <code>horizontally</code> and <code>diagonally</code>.</p>  <p>So basically, there is a link from number <code>1 to 9</code> (or maximum number - e.g. if board is a <strong>4x4</strong>, then from <code>1 to 16</code>).</p>